{
  "stem": "1169.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I heard about Zionist once in my home, when somebody told me I want to teach you a secret-- one of these boys who was my home-- and he taught me the first Hebrew song, called [SPEAKING HEBREW], which is my favorite song to this day.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But he said, don't tell your parents I taught you this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Zionism was not that much part of life, but it became the-- the number one topic in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And it's the first time I heard of a date in Jewish history, I had never heard of before, and that date is November 2, 1917-- the Balfour Declaration.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I never heard of that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I learned about it in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And there was his holy sage, the Rabbi of Debrecen-- the true Rabbi of Debrecen-- who every day, all day, went around saying that God is punishing us because we neglected Israel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We neglected [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was no question about that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "If we ever get out, there's only one place to go to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It's Israel.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And everyone there was a Zionist, even the sages who people think they were not, there was no doubt over there that they were.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "You know, in a trench, everybody believes in God.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And in Bergen-Belsen, everybody was a Zionist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There came the holidays, the high holidays-- Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We had only the one [SPEAKING HEBREW], or prayer book, for the high holidays for 1,850 people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And the rabbis of Bergen-Belsen unanimously decided that the whole camp should learn one prayer by heart, that when we pray, at least this one prayer everybody should say in unison.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And this prayer was called [SPEAKING HEBREW], which is part of the high holidays service.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
